# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# RED TEAMING FRAMEWORK — Environment Variables
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this file to .env and fill in values for your setup.
#
# Only fill the sections for the frameworks you use:
#   - Using PyRIT only?  → Fill PyRIT + Reports sections
#   - Using Garak only?  → Fill Garak + Reports sections
#   - Using both?        → Fill everything
#
# Variables marked [DEFAULT] have sensible defaults and can be omitted.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── PyRIT Attacker LLM (required for PyRIT campaigns) ─────
# The LLM that generates adversarial prompts (plays the attacker role).

# Endpoint URL of your attacker LLM service (e.g., Ollama, OpenAI, Azure)
PYRIT_ATTACKER_ENDPOINT=<YOUR_ATTACKER_ENDPOINT>

# Model name/ID to use for the attacker LLM
PYRIT_ATTACKER_MODEL=<YOUR_ATTACKER_MODEL>

# API key for authentication to the attacker LLM service.
# You can set a static key here, OR use the COMMAND variant below
# to resolve a key dynamically (e.g., refresh a JWT token).
PYRIT_ATTACKER_API_KEY=<YOUR_ATTACKER_API_KEY>

# [OPTIONAL] Shell command that prints the API key to stdout.
# If set, this command is executed at runtime and its output replaces
# the static PYRIT_ATTACKER_API_KEY value.
# Example: PYRIT_ATTACKER_API_KEY_COMMAND="python scripts/get_token.py"
# PYRIT_ATTACKER_API_KEY_COMMAND=

# ── PyRIT Scorer LLM (required for PyRIT campaigns) ───────
# The LLM that evaluates target responses (JSON structured output).
# Tip: use a model good at structured JSON (e.g. gpt-4o, llama3.1:8b).

# Endpoint URL of your scorer LLM service
PYRIT_SCORER_ENDPOINT=<YOUR_SCORER_ENDPOINT>

# Model name/ID to use for the scorer LLM
PYRIT_SCORER_MODEL=<YOUR_SCORER_MODEL>

# API key for authentication to the scorer LLM service.
PYRIT_SCORER_API_KEY=<YOUR_SCORER_API_KEY>

# [OPTIONAL] Shell command for dynamic scorer key resolution (same logic
# as PYRIT_ATTACKER_API_KEY_COMMAND).
# PYRIT_SCORER_API_KEY_COMMAND=

# ── PyRIT Runtime (required for PyRIT campaigns) ──────────
# [DEFAULT] Database file path for PyRIT to store attack results and state
PYRIT_DB_PATH=pyrit.db

# [DEFAULT] Delay (in seconds) for gracefully shutting down event loops
# PYRIT_LOOP_SHUTDOWN_DELAY=0.3

# [DEFAULT] Maximum number of concurrent tasks when processing datasets
# PYRIT_DATASET_MAX_CONCURRENCY=5

# ── Reports (always required) ─────────────────────────────
# [DEFAULT] Directory path where JSON reports will be stored
JSON_REPORTS_DIR=reports

# ── Garak (required for Garak campaigns) ──────────────────
# Directory path where Garak stores its reports
GARAK_REPORTS_DIR=<YOUR_GARAK_REPORTS_DIR>

# Path to the Garak configuration JSON file (auto-generated before each run)
GARAK_CONFIG_PATH=config/garak_config.json

# [DEFAULT] Request timeout (in seconds) for Garak API calls
# GARAK_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=60

# [DEFAULT] Prefix for Garak report output files
# GARAK_DEFAULT_REPORT_PREFIX=reports/run
